1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Bilbil heydar wan dikê
 
The nightingale sings over there

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Bîna we tê
 
Your scent reaches us

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Bilbil heydar wan dikê
 
The nightingale sings over there

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Ax Efrînê
 
Oh Afrin

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Efrînê, Efrînê, navdar e, tu şêrîn e
 
Afrin, Afrin, it is famous, you are sweet

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Delala min biha ye
 
My precious, dear

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Bihuşta vê dinê
 
The paradise of this world

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Efrînê, Efrînê, navdar e, tu şêrîn e
 
Afrin, Afrin, it is famous, you are sweet

9
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Delala min biha ye
 
My precious, dear

10
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Bihuşta vê dinê
 
The paradise of this world

11
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Piriskek ji dara zeytûnê
 
A spark from the olive tree

12
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Keda bav û kalên me
 
The effort of our forefathers

13
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Nanê sêlê çiqas xweş e
 
How delicious is the saj bread

14
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Ji destê dayîkên me
 
From the hands of our mothers

15
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Piriskek ji dara zeytûnê
 
A spark from the olive tree

16
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Keda bav û kalên me
 
The effort of our forefathers

17
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Nanê sêlê çiqas xweş e
 
How delicious is the saj bread

18
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Ji destê dayîkên me
 
From the hands of our mothers

19
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Apê min silav, merheba, çawa yî?
 
Greetings uncle, hello, how are you?

20
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Merheba. Ehlen û sehlen.
 
Hello. Welcome.

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Hûn bi xêr hatin. Ser serî, ser çava.
 
Welcome. Upon my head, upon my eyes.

22
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Hûn bi xêr hatin nav vî welatî. Ev axa pîroz e.
 
Welcome to this country. This is a blessed land.

23
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Ser serî û ser çava. Spas. Înşellah serkeftin ji we re.
 
Upon my head and eyes. Thank you. God willing, success to
you.

24
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Spas.
 
Thank you.

25
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Apê min... di destpêkê de...
 
Uncle... in the beginning...

26
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Ev cara sêyem e em derbasî gundên Meydanê dibin.
 
This is the third time we are visiting the villages of
Meydan.

27
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Carekî em hatin Gawanda. Carekê em çûn Sêmala.
 
Once we came to Gawanda. Once we went to Semala.

28
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Naha jî em derbasî gundê Dûdê bûn, wisa ne?
 
And now we have entered the village of Dude, right?

29
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Ser seran hatin. Ser çavan hatin. Ehlen û sehlen.
 
You have come upon my head. You have come upon my eyes.
Welcome.

30
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Wê spas. Çawa ye, tu baş î?
 
Thank you. How are you, are you doing well?

31
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Spas dikim, we jî.
 
I thank you, you too.

32
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Em ê bixwazin em gundê Dûdê jî nas bikin.
 
We would like to get to know the village of Dude as well.

33
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Em dixwazin di destpêkê de nas bikin, navê gundê we ji kû
hatiye?
 
At the beginning we want to know, where did the name of your
village come from?

34
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Navê gundê me, em eslê wê dema ku gund nişîn dibin...
 
The name of our village, originally when the village was
being settled...

35
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Xelk derbasî rojhilatê vê hatine.
 
The people passed towards the east of this place.

36
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Paşê da, ev gund nişîn dibe... Gund... di qontarê palekî de
bû...
 
Afterwards, this village became settled... The village... it
was at the foothills of a hill...

37
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Dikeve nav newala gundê Ecer.
 
It falls into the valley of the village of Ecer.

38
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Cihê vî gundî, gellek fireh bû.
 
The place of this village was very spacious.

39
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Gundekî wek meselê muxtarek hebû. Muxtarî Kerîm bû.
 
A village for example had a mukhtar. It was Mukhtar Kerim.

40
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Camêr bû û cih belaş bû.
 
He was a brave man and the place was free.

41
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Xerîb û xulmet digirtin. Digotin em herin vî gundî cih
bigirin.
 
They took in strangers and servants. People said, let's go
to this village and settle down.

42
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Li vir va dihatin, ji geliyê Meydanê ve dihatin.
 
Here they came, they came from the valley of Meydan.

43
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Digotin ev kîjan gund e? Gundî meselê... gundî camêr...
 
They said, which village is this? For example... the brave
man's village...

44
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Ku ev mirov û eşya li gundî digirtin.
 
When people and belongings were accommodated in the village.

45
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Gotin gundî Dûdê.
 
They called it the village of Dude.

46
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Hîn jî Dûdê bû, an çi wextê gotin... çawa gava ew hatin.
 
Was it already Dude, or when did they say it... when they
arrived.

47
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Mesele çawa ber bi sînor tiştan ne bû?
 
How did things move towards the border?

48
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Çawa ber sînorên tinebû... em gî yek sînor di nav de tune
bûn.
 
How the borders didn't exist... we were all one, there were
no borders between us.

49
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Em niha nêzîkî heşt kîlometran dûrî sînor in e.
 
Right now we are about eight kilometers away from the
border.

50
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Ha wisa... hûn ji vir da hatin. Pirs kirin... gotin ev gund
çi gund e?
 
Ah like that... you came from here. They asked... they said
what village is this?

51
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Gundê Ecer bi nav e. Gotin gund yek e, na, ê duduya.
 
It's named the village of Ecer. They said is it the first
village, no, the second one.

52
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Yanî navê gundê we, ji hejmara didu hatiye? Yê diduyan
hatiye?
 
Meaning the name of your village comes from the number two?
It came from the second one?

53
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Ê duduya hatiye.
 
It came from the second one.

54
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Paşê bû Dûdê.
 
Then it became Dude.

55
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Paşê bû Dûdê.
 
Then it became Dude.

56
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Çi mane ye "Dûdê"?
 
What is the meaning of "Dude"?

57
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Welleh îşta, wek mîrat çi bûye.
 
Well, as a habit it's become like an inheritance.

58
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Belê, dema Osmanî derbasî Sûriyê bû, ew rejîma Be's de
derbas bû.
 
Yes, when the Ottomans crossed into Syria, when the Ba'ath
regime took over.

59
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Navên gundên me bi hatin guhertin, yanî Tirkan gorî xwe nav
kir û rejîma Be's gorî xwe...
 
The names of our villages were changed, I mean the Turks
named it their way, and the Ba'ath regime their way...

60
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Di wê demê de nav hatin guhertin?
 
Were the names changed at that time?

61
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Na î me nav nehatin guhertin.
 
No, ours did not have its name changed.

62
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Her ji duduya, bû Dûdê.
 
From duduya (second), it became Dude.

63
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Erê, ji duduya bû Dûdê.
 
Yes, from duduya (second), it became Dude.

64
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Bû Dûdê.
 
It became Dude.

65
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Ê gundê we... bi giştî malbat in. Te qet kîjan malbatên
dî...
 
And your village... in general they are families. Have you
any other families...

66
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Gundê me, serî de, malbatek bû.
 
Our village, at the beginning, was one family.

67
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Malbata, digotin Mela Mehemedê Dado.
 
The family, they called them Mela Mehemedê Dado.

68
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Ewana çar bira bûn, piştî wî bûn çar malbat... Her birayek
meselê paşê xerîb jî hatin...
 
They were four brothers, after that they became four
families... Each brother for instance, later strangers also
came...

69
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Dema ku ew çar malbat bûn gund e. Di derve hatin pênc
malbat, bûn pênc şeş malbat hatin tev me bûn û pirr bûn.
 
When those four families made up the village. Five families
came from outside, they became five or six families coming
to join us and grew a lot.

70
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Yanî pêşî de ew malbatek bûn... piştî we malbat belav bûn.
 
Meaning at first they were one family... after that the
family expanded.

71
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Erê... ji wê malbatê gîş bûn çar. Û ew çar malbat jî paşê
xelk ji derve hatin ser wê malbatê.
 
Yes... from that family all of them became four. And those
four families too, later people from outside came upon that
family.

72
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Serkêşê wê malbatê... digotin Mela Mehemedê Dado.
 
The head of that family... they called him Mela Mehemedê
Dado.

73
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Û ew malbat din jî navê wane kîjan in?
 
And the other families, what are their names?

74
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Pêşî de, siftehî malbata qedîm... Malbata Mela Mehemedê Dado
ye.
 
At the beginning, the oldest initial family... The Mela
Mehemedê Dado family.

75
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Ewana çar bira bûn... mezinê wan jî, Mehemedê Dado.
 
They were four brothers... and their elder, Mehemedê Dado.

76
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Malbat qesim bû, bûn çar bira. Her malbatek... navek lê
nanin.
 
The family divided, they became four brothers. Every
family... put a name on it.

77
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Yek... malbata, digotin Çûçeleran.
 
One... family, they called them the Chuçeleran.

78
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Yek malbata, dibên Teraşleran.
 
One family, they call the Terashleran.

79
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Yek dibên malbata Mehlero.
 
One they call the Mehlero family.

80
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Paşê nav, li dervê hatin. Malbatên din hatin tev me bûn.
 
Then names, they came from outside. Other families came and
joined us.

81
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Malbatek hat digotin Mela Bêrîqudê.
 
A family came called Mela Bêrîqudê.

82
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Malbatek hat, çaxê hatin... gotin kîjan gund e, hatin
tiştekî wisa nedîtin.
 
A family came, when they came... they asked which village it
is, they came and didn't see anything like it.

83
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Li rojhilatê da hatin, pirs kirin... gotin we li gundê Dûdê
bi vê derê be.
 
They came from the east, they asked... they were told it's
the village of Dude over here.

84
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Mala Hecî Mehemed wê da demin...
 
Mala Heci Mehemed settled there...

85
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Hatin û tev me bûn. Li rojavayê da hatin, Mala Bêrîqudê
digotinê, hatin tev me bûn.
 
They came and joined us. They came from the west, they were
called Mala Bêrîqudê, they came and joined us.

86
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Paşê digotin Mala Hesûlero... maleke bi navê Hesûlero.
 
Then they said Mala Hesûlero... a family named Hesûlero.

87
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Li Gawandayê re hatin, malbatek tev me bûn.
 
They came through Gawanda, a family joined us.

88
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Paşê... gotin malbatên din... yanî çar pênc malbat wina pênc
şeş hatin tev me bûn, û gund mezin bûye.
 
Then... they said other families... meaning four or five
families like that, five or six came and joined us, and the
village became big.

89
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Apê min... li herêma Meydanê ta niha heft gund hene?
 
My uncle... are there currently seven villages in the region
of Meydan?

90
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

91
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Ê kîjan gund, berî kîjan avabûye te zanî ta niha?
 
And which village was established before which? Have you
known this so far?

92
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Welleh ez nizanim, yek wîkî çawa em dizanin, tarîxek bi me
tune.
 
Well I don't know, one thing we know is that, we don't have
a history log.

93
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Xwendina me tune. Tarîx cem me tune ye.
 
We don't have literacy. We don't have history records.

94
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Rihmetliyê Xaşû, tarîxek wek xeber didan, karek digotin
Xaşû.
 
The late Xasho, he used to tell a bit of history, a guy
called Xasho.

95
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Digotin wê wextek bê... Tirk wê xwe bi qeşmerî çil dewletî
be.
 
He used to say a time will come... The Turks will make a
fool out of forty countries.

96
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Yanî Tirkan qasî wî wekî... nav û dengê wan di ceng da
derketibû.
 
I mean the Turks, just like he said... their fame had spread
throughout the battle.

97
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Digot Tirko ku wekî rûvî be... wê wek qeşmerê çil dewletî
be.
 
He said a Turk is like a fox... he will be making a fool out
of forty countries.

98
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Min ev tarîx, ev xeber li wan guhdar dikir.
 
I would listen to this history, these words from them.

99
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Digotin wê şer li rojhilat ve rabe... wê xwîn wek avê be...
 
They used to say a war will arise from the east... blood
will flow like water...

100
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Çi kuştin, çi tişt û hemî dinê werin guhertin.
 
Such killings, such things and everything in the world will
be changed.

101
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Belê... paşê digotin tecahilî wê were...
 
Yes... then they said ignorance would come...

102
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Tecahilî ew... em dizanin Rûs û ew tişt e... ev dê gî tiştî
ku niha sirrin an na?
 
That ignorance... we know it's Russia and those things...
are all these things a secret now or not?

103
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Jixwe dema Rûs di nav me de bûn... ez çawa tiştan tarîx wilo
ji wan hîn bûme.
 
After all, when the Russians were among us... that's how I
learned history things like this from them.

104
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Lê min wek emrê xwe me eyan kir ku xwendin tune... ev e
tiştên em zanin.
 
But as for my age, I have established that there is no
literacy... this is what we know.

105
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Ne... rojhilatê gund, Gawanda ye. Rojava we gund çi ye?
 
No... east of the village is Gawanda. What village is west
of yours?

106
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Gundo Welîkliya ye.
 
It is the village of Welikliya.

107
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Welîkliya ye?
 
Is it Welikliya?

108
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,000
Erê, Welîkliya ye.
 
Yes, it is Welikliya.

109
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:37,000
Di Meydanan de ev gund bi ser hev in?
 
In Meydan, are these villages adjacent to each other?

110
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Erê, erê. Siftehî Gawanda. Paşê Dûdê, paşê Welîkliya, paşê
Qurrê, paşê Tepe Qirê...
 
Yes, yes. First Gawanda. Then Dude, then Welikliya, then
Qurre, then Tepe Qire...

111
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Paşê gundê Miskêta, paşê Sêmala. Hemî li ser xetê ne.
 
Then the village of Misketa, then Semala. They are all on
the border line.

112
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Sêmala. Naxwe gundê we jî nêzîkî sînor e. Ev sînorê... ser
xetê û bin xetê... we meriv li wir hene?
 
Semala. Therefore your village is also close to the border.
This border... on the border and below the border... do you
have relatives there?

113
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Gî merivê me ne. Niha dêya min gî li ser sînorê wan a...
 
They are all our relatives. Right now my mother is from
across their border...

114
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Li kîjan gundî ye?
 
In which village is it?

115
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Gundê wan deran, dibêjinê Dîlo... Menteqeya Qedere.
 
The village around there, they call it Dilo... The region of
Qedere.

116
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Dêya min ji wê derê ye. Bavê min wextê ku eskertî... de
çawîş bû. Cendirme bû.
 
My mother is from there. My father, during his military
service... was a sergeant. He was a gendarme.

117
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Wextê... Osmanî.
 
During the time... of the Ottomans.

118
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Esker bû... Wexta ku pêşiya me çûye ji xwe re aniye.
 
He was a soldier... Back in our early days he went and
brought her for himself.

119
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Ev gund e hemî... merivê hev in?
 
All of this village... they are all relatives?

120
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Na, wextê sînor ketin navberê da, gelo ji gundê we... an
yekî li vir man, yek li wî alî ma?
 
Well, when the border was put between them, did anyone from
your village... or some stay here, and some stay on that
side?

121
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Ê li vir bûn, li vir man. Yê li wê derê, li wê derê man. Û
pirr mal hebûn...
 
The ones who were here, stayed here. The ones who were
there, stayed there. And there were many families...

122
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Çend malbat ji gundê me ji vir çûn û li wê derê bûn...
 
A few families from our village went from here and were over
there...

123
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Dema ku sînor kete navbera... her kes ma li ciyê xwe.
 
When the border fell between us... everyone stayed in their
own place.

124
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:37,000
Apê min... wekî di nava gundê we de... gundiyan derketiye?
 
Uncle... as in your village... have the villagers left?

125
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Welleh pirranî derketiye. Naxwe pirranî derketine.
 
Well, the majority has left. Of course the majority has
left.

126
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Hîn ji zeman ve... pêncî sal berî wê, şêst sal berî wê...
deh sal berî wê...
 
Even from a long time ago... fifty years ago, sixty years
ago... ten years ago...

127
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Bîst sal... pirranî milet derketiye ji gund.
 
Twenty years... most of the people have left the village.

128
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Ê ku de berê xwe dane... ber bi kû ve?
 
And those who headed out... where to?

129
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Berê xwe gellek ji wan dane Ewropayê... çûne dewletê Xerîb.
Ber bi Ewropayê çûne.
 
Many of them headed towards Europe... they went to Western
states. They went towards Europe.

130
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Nîvê millet di çar aliyê cîhanê de ne.
 
Half of the people are in the four corners of the world.

131
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,000
Yanî niha piranî maye li ku? Li Swîsreyê ne?
 
Meaning right now where are the most of them staying? Are
they in Switzerland?

132
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Li Swîsre in.
 
They are in Switzerland.

133
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Û ê din?
 
And the others?

134
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Milletê din jî niha hemî... lawê min tenê, pêncî şexs ji wî
gundî ser pêncî di heman demê re tabî... wekî wê bêtir, bes
li Swîsreyê ne.
 
All the other people right now... my son alone, fifty people
from this village, over fifty, of course... even more than
that, are just in Switzerland.

135
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Ji ser pêncî si sal dî re... Bas li Almanyayê ne, li
Holendayê ne, û li Tirkiyê jî yanî...
 
Over fifty, thirty more years... They are just in Germany,
in the Netherlands, and in Turkey too, meaning...

136
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
Li her welatekî ku têda çûne... malbat tiştên xwe çêkirine.
 
In every country they went into... families built their own
things.

137
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Kes ji gundiyên we... li Reco ne an li Efrînê, tine ne?
 
Does anyone from your villagers... live in Rajo or in Afrin,
are there none?

138
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Qet tinne ne. Li Efrînê hesab e qet, li Reco nîne.
 
There are none at all. Counting in Afrin not at all, in Rajo
there are none.

139
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Li Helebê bi hesin e... Li bajarê Şêre waha... Meydan Ekbez!
 
In Aleppo it's solid... In the city of Sherawa over there...
Midan Akbis!

140
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Meydan Ekbez pirr in... ekserî Meydan Ekbez nîvîsê xelkî
gundê me ne.
 
Midan Akbis has a lot... mostly Midan Akbis, half of the
people of our village are there.

141
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Belê Meydan Ekbez... ji hemî Meydanan pirtir hene?
 
Yes Midan Akbis... does it have more from all of Meydan?

142
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Erê... pir gundî me nin... paşê gundê Xelîl Pîrko, Qûse,
Meydana gîşt... bas li gundê me pirrtir in.
 
Yes... a lot of our villagers... then the village of Xelil
Pirko, Quse, all of Meydan... but there are more in our
village.

143
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Na, wek gundê we, bi tevahî çend mal in? Pêncî mal hene?
 
Now, as your village, how many houses are there in total?
Are there fifty houses?

144
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Welleh na ev bû pêncî. Berî wê bîst neh bûn, sî bûn, niha bû
pêncî. Pêncî mal in.
 
Well right now it's become fifty. Before it was twenty-nine,
it was thirty, now it's fifty. They are fifty houses.

145
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Lê eger tu hesabê wanî derketî bikî... ew sê sed mal, çar
sed mal gişt derketin, xaliye.
 
But if you calculate the ones who left... those three
hundred houses, four hundred houses all left, it's empty.

146
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Ew tenê yên niha hene pêncî ne.
 
Those right now are only fifty.

147
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Ê wek gundê we... debara xwe bi çi dikir?
 
And your village... how did it make a living?

148
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Welle debara me... reze, zeytûne, kiraze û yanî heywan in.
Pez, tişt in...
 
Well our livelihood... is vineyards, olives, cherries, and
well, animals. Sheep, things like that...

149
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Her kes debara xwe pê dikin.
 
Everyone makes their living from it.

150
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Ê gundê we de kanî heye?
 
Does your village have a spring?

151
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Kanî? Kanî tinne, anku avên esasî wek çem tinne.
 
A spring? There is no spring, meaning main water sources
like a river are non-existent.

152
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Lê kaniyek heye li wê derê, li başûrê rojavayê gund, kaniyek
mezin heye, yê ku Fransiyan çêkiribû.
 
But there is a spring over there, in the southwest of the
village, there is a big spring, the one that the French
built.

153
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Bîst metre kûrbûna wê ye û deh metre firehbûna wê heye.
 
It has twenty meters of depth and it has ten meters of
width.

154
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Û li wê derê jî, pêşiya gundî bi wî aliyê rê ve... dîwarek
heye.
 
And also over there, in front of the village on that side of
the road... there is a wall.

155
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,000
Berê jê re digotin bajarekî ku meşa... sêsed gav dûr e.
 
Back in the day they called it a city that you walk... three
hundred steps away.

156
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,000
Gundê ku li ser gir e... bîrek kevn li serê çiyê ye. Cihên
qedîm e.
 
The village that is on the hill... an old well is on top of
the mountain. It's an ancient place.

157
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Carekî em çûyîn e...
 
Once we went...

158
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

159
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Cihê qedîm e.
 
It's an ancient place.

160
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Cihê qedîm e.
 
It's an ancient place.

161
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Efrînê navê wê çi bû feda? A sor a navê wê çi bû lê? Ka ew
navê wê ne... mirîşkên Xantût di urfê de heye.
 
What was the name of the one from Afrin, feda? What was the
name of the red one? Well, those are its names... Xantut
chickens exist in the tradition.

162
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Gelek spas, mala te ava be.
 
Thank you very much, bless your house.

163
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Mala we jî ava be, ser seran ser çavan.
 
Bless your house too, you are very welcome.

164
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Gundê Meydanê ya Raco, kantona Efrînê, 8 kîlometreyan li
bakurê navçeya Raco, 53 kîlometreyan li bakurê bajarê Efrînê
dikeve.
 
The village of Meydan in Raco, Afrin canton, is located 8
kilometers north of the Raco district, and 53 kilometers
north of the city of Afrin.

165
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Gundê Meydanan ji heft gundan pêk tê. Gawenda, Welîkliya,
Gazê, Kurê, Miskê, Sêmala û Dudê.
 
Meydanan consists of seven villages. Gawenda, Welikliya,
Gaze, Kure, Miske, Semala, and Dude.

166
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Gundê Dudê li deşta golê ya Meydanan dikeve.
 
Dude village is located in the Gole plain of Meydanan.

167
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:02,000
Navê gund ji wateya dudo yan ku du hatiye.
 
The name of the village comes from the meaning of "dudo,"
which means two.

168
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Ji ber ku ew gund ji her du aliyan, rojhilat û rojava ve,
gundê duyemîn e ji nav gundên Meydana.
 
Because the village is the second village among the Meydanan
villages from both the east and the west.

169
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:28,000
Malbata Mihemedê Dudê weke yekemîn malbat li gund
rûniştîbûye.
 
The family of Mihemedê Dudê was the first family to settle
in the village.

170
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,000
Qewet be ji we re.
 
More power to you.

171
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Merheba.
 
Hello.

172
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,000
Merheba ji we re. Qewet be ji we re.
 
Hello to you. More power to you.

173
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Saet xweş, merheba.
 
Welcome, hello.

174
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,000
Ehlen xalo, saet xweş.
 
Welcome uncle, have a good time.

175
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Merheba ji we re. Qewet be ji we re.
 
Hello to you. More power to you.

176
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,000
Sax bî.
 
Be well.

177
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:10,000
Saeta we xweş be. Gotin hûn gelek tiştan çêdikin, de em
hatin we tiriyê xwe beraf kirî ye.
 
Have a good time. They said you make a lot of things, so we
came; you have harvested your grapes.

178
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,000
Erê, me tirî beraf kir.
 
Yes, we harvested the grapes.

179
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:15,000
Em kurmanc in, em karê xwe çêdikin, qirmiyên xwe çêdikin.
 
We are Kurds, we do our own work, we make our fruit pulps
(qirme).

180
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,000
Em meywînatê çêdikin, em kemînê wê çêdikin.
 
We make fruit leathers, we make its foam.

181
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:24,000
Em rezan qut dikin, cûz el-hind tê de dikin, simîd tê de
dikin, em qirmiyên xwe çêdikin.
 
We cut the rice, we put coconut in it, we put semolina in
it, we make our fruit pulps.

182
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Me çû tiriyê xwe beraf kir, cîh û filan çêkir, me keland, em
kê çêdikin.
 
We went and collected our grapes, prepared the place and so
on, we boiled it, we make them.

183
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Naha we dema tiriyê xwe xelas kiriye?
 
Now have you finished your grape season?

184
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Eh me li wê nokê de xelas kirî ye.
 
Yes, we finished it at that point.

185
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:44,000
Erê, me tirî çinî, me pişt re me maqsera hanî me dims çêkir,
me sunciq jî çêkir, naha ji vî dimsî dor dora qirmê ye.
 
Yes, we harvested the grapes, then we brought the grape
press and made molasses, we also made sunciq, now from this
molasses it's the turn for fruit pulp.

186
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
Naha dor dora qirmê ye? Hûn wê çawa çêdikin?
 
Now it's the turn for the fruit pulp? How do you make this?

187
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
Em pê qirmê çêdikin.
 
We make fruit pulp with it.

188
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Ev qirme hene, ev e...
 
These are fruit pulps, this...

189
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,000
Ka kîjanê ji me re ser da kê?
 
Which one will you show us?

190
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,000
Hê ev, ev e.
 
Here, this one.

191
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
Navê vê çi ye tê gotin? Ha ev qirme ye.
 
What is the name of this? Oh this is fruit pulp.

192
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Naha ev we çawa çêkiriye?
 
Now how did you make this?

193
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:01,000
Ev me simîd tê kiriye, me cûz el-hind tê kiriye, me behîv tê
kiriye.
 
We put semolina in it, we put coconut in it, we put almonds
in it.

194
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Me yê mayî nekiriye, min kuncî tê kiriye, me behîv û tiştên
wisa tê kiriye.
 
We didn't put the rest, I put sesame, we put almonds and
things like that.

195
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,000
Ev mûj in a?
 
Are these raisins?

196
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Ew jî mûj in a.
 
Those are raisins too.

197
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
Ev jî mûj in e?
 
Are these also raisins?

198
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,000
Ew jî mûj in a.
 
Those are raisins too.

199
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Ev mûj in ku em zeytê dikin û sûd ê wê heye, û em tiriyê xwe
dikin.
 
These are raisins that we add oil to and it has benefits,
and we put our grapes.

200
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,000
Ev ê îsal in an yê par in?
 
Are these from this year or last year?

201
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,000
Ev ê îsal in, ê îsal in.
 
These are from this year, from this year.

202
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Ev çi ye?
 
What is this?

203
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,000
Ewnan meywîne ne, em kî wan dore kin.
 
Those are dried fruits, we will wrap them.

204
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Ew ên ho ne... ew kin e. Ew jî kuncî ne.
 
Those are like that... that's short. Those are also sesame.

205
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:29,000
Ew jî kuncî ne. Û ewe jî li wir.
 
Those are also sesame. And that one there.

206
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Ew jî...
 
That too...

207
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Ew jî darçîn e.
 
That is cinnamon too.

208
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Ew jî darçîn e.
 
That is cinnamon too.

209
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Ewnan rêşin, em ê kî dore kin a.
 
Those are dark, we will wrap them.

210
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Hûn ê kî dore kin a qirmê?
 
You will wrap the fruit pulp?

211
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Kê dore ke vê qirmê. Erê ew qirme ye.
 
Who will wrap this fruit pulp. Yes, that is fruit pulp.

212
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Ka ewa tiştên ... Tê naha şerbetê dikelînî?
 
Well those things... Are you boiling the syrup now?

213
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:55,000
Erê ez şerbetê dikelînim. Û naha bi kel ket em ê kî simîd tê
kin.
 
Yes I boil the syrup. And now it started to boil, we will
put semolina in.

214
00:13:55,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Û em ê kî tiştî dikin nav, çem ê kî tê kin naha hûn ê
bibînin.
 
And we will put things into it, you will see what we put in
now.

215
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,000
Baş e.
 
Alright.

216
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Dayê baş e. Heta em tiştekî bibînin... behsa sunciq kirin.
 
Mother alright. Let's see something... they mentioned
sunciq.

217
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Gotin sunciq jî çêdikin, li ku derê ye?
 
They said you also make sunciq, where is it?

218
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Em sunciq jî çêdikin, ewe jî li cem e. Hûn ê bibînin.
 
We also make sunciq, that is also here. You will see.

219
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:24,000
Em sunciq jî çêdikin, ew jî li cem me ye, li wir e.
 
We make sunciq too, that's also with us, it's over there.

220
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Merheba ji we re. Qewet be ji we re.
 
Hello to you. More power to you.

221
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Ehlen, merheba. Destên we sax bin.
 
Welcome, hello. Bless your hands.

222
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Qewet be ji we re.
 
More power to you.

223
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Xwedê te sax ke.
 
May God keep you healthy.

224
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,000
Hûn li vir sunciqan çêdikin? Vana jî sunciqan çêdikin?
 
Are you making sunciq here? Are these also making sunciq?

225
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Erê em sunciqan çêdikin.
 
Yes we make sunciq.

226
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Çawa çêdikin a?
 
How do you make them?

227
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Ev sunciqî em çêdikin manî zivistanê.
 
We make this sunciq for the winter.

228
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:51,000
Em ditirsin mesel e xela bibe, zarokên me hez bikin, ne pê
de temam bibin.
 
We are afraid for instance there might be a scarcity, our
children might want it, and not find it.

229
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:55,000
Pê xwedî didin biharê dixwin. Ev şîraniyên kurdan e.
 
We keep it and eat it in the spring. This is the sweets of
the Kurds.

230
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:59,000
Şîraniyên kevin e.
 
It's an old sweet.

231
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Baş e çawa çêdikin? Hûn têdikin avê, ji min re bêjin.
 
Alright how do you make it? You put it in water, tell me.

232
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Em haran pêşî tirî diçinin, dînên malê. Me serî de we
bicilifînin...
 
We first harvest the grapes, bring them home. We separate
them from the stems...

233
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Em ê axa gewr lê xin, ha serî we tiyî kin, em ê kî
biçilifînin.
 
We add white earth to it, put it on top, we will squeeze it.

234
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:19,000
Em ê wê bînin dîsan, paşê da ava bikişînin di qozqankan de.
Û bikelînin.
 
We will bring it again, then extract the juice in cauldrons.
And boil it.

235
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Kêl ket... edî nîn we darê. Û paşê sar bibe, saetekê
dudiya...
 
Once it boils... then put the wood on it. And then it cools
down, for an hour or two...

236
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,000
Û paşê dînin varên sizmik kin.
 
And then we bring them and strain them.

237
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,000
Û di sê ro pişta jî em bînin gûzan bi deziyan xînin, û em ê
wê hazir bikin.
 
And three days later we bring walnuts and thread them on
strings, and we prepare them.

238
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Û em ê çing xînin, vî dezî pê re bê girêdan.
 
And we put them in pots, tying the string to it.

239
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,000
Naha da ava çi ye? Kuncî ye têde?
 
Now what is that liquid? Is it sesame in there?

240
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Ewa nîşa ye. Em ê dînin varên bikelînin.
 
That is starch. We bring it and boil it.

241
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:41,000
Û ev nîşa jî... tiştekek bidin navê, paşê em pelûl bikin.
 
And this starch too... we put something in it, then we make
pudding.

242
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Em ê bînin varên vê aunate tê da kin... Vê gûzê de...
 
We bring this stuff and put it in... In this walnut...

243
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Naha ev dimsê tirî ye?
 
Now is this grape molasses?

244
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Ev dimsê tirî ye lê. Şerbet e.
 
Yes, this is grape molasses. It is syrup.

245
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Paşê em ê kî pelûl bikin a...
 
It is syrup.

246
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Paşê em ê kî pelûl bikin a...
 
Then we will make pudding with it...

247
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Çend saetan we xwest ev a?
 
How many hours did this take you?

248
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Havo... yanî şeş saetan şerbeta xwe dikelîne... saeteka..
 
That... I mean about six hours of its syrup boils... an
hour..

249
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:05,000
Û paşê hawa jî çi yek deh deqîqeyan... rîbe saetekê be, em ê
kî pelûl kin... Û tîr dibe.
 
And then that too takes about ten minutes... or fifteen
minutes to make pudding... And it gets thick.

250
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:10,000
Û em bînin vê avê tê de kin... Naha em çêkin.
 
And we bring it and put this liquid in... Now we make it.

251
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:13,000
Naha paşî we vê ta va keye? Sûnciqan?
 
Now after this, you dipped it in? The sunciq?

252
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Havo em di nav lewitê de av dikin... Havo çar pênc nava av
dikin hetanî temam dibe.
 
That is dipped in the paste... That is dipped four or five
times until it's finished.

253
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Û rokê sibe tê de dikin.
 
And in the morning it's set out.

254
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:28,000
Û carekê jî, êvarê.. du caran jî nîvro û êvarê... sibe û
nîvro û êvarê... sê ro tê de dikin...
 
And once in the evening.. twice in the afternoon and
evening.. morning, afternoon, and evening... it's dipped for
three days...

255
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:33,000
Heta hişk bibe, roja dîsa sibe tê de dikin... Û tişta heta
na hişk bibe...
 
Until it dries, put out again the next morning... And until
it completely dries...

256
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Vê naha we dawî kir?
 
You finished this now?

257
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Av xwedî dawî kir, em gelek sekinîn... em baş nermê şixul
dikin...
 
We are done now, we worked a lot... we work on it softly...

258
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,000
Darikê derdixin, em dibin ser hewşê...
 
We take out the sticks, we bring them to the courtyard...

259
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:48,000
Heta xelas dibe... Çar qor, pênc qor em lê dixin.
 
Until it finishes... Four times, five times we dip it.

260
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Naha we çend qor lê xistiye?
 
Now how many times have you dipped it?

261
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Naha me, çar qor lê xistiye.
 
Now we, we have dipped it four times.

262
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Ev ê giştî çend qora we dixinê?
 
In total how many times do you dip them?

263
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,000
Heta bîst qora lê dikeve.
 
It gets dipped up to twenty times.

264
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Naha tiştekî din... min dît.. gotin.. gundê Meydanê li
Efrînê ne..
 
Now something else... I saw... they said... this is Meydan
village in Afrin..

265
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Bes dema tu dibê sunciq ew dibêjin Meydana çêdike yan gundê
Badîna.
 
But when you say sunciq they say Meydan makes it or Badina
village.

266
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Ev bi wan tên naskirin. Tu çend sal in sunciqan çêdikî?
 
It is known by them. How many years have you been making
sunciq?

267
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Ez... Meydan pênc şeş sal e na em çêdikin, ez nû hatim
vir...
 
I... Meydan, we have been making it for five or six years, I
just came here...

268
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:19,000
Ber mala me rûniştim... min dît ev milet karê xwe dikir...
 
I stayed with my family... I saw the people here doing their
work...

269
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Siftê min haşkokir, paşê min baş kar kir...
 
First I prepared myself, then I worked well on it...

270
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Naha gund gîştî sunciqan çêdikin?
 
Now does the whole village make sunciq?

271
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Na hinek gund çêdikin. Razi gişta tenê.
 
No, part of the village makes it. The rest doesn't.

272
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Vê dawiya difroşin jî... bo firotanê ye yan bo mala xwe
çêdikin?
 
Do you sell it afterwards... is it for selling or do you
make it for your home?

273
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Welle em siftê ji firotanê re çêdikir, bes niha em bo mala
xwe çêdikim.
 
Well we initially made it for selling, but now we make it
for our home.

274
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Ez nafiroşim.
 
I don't sell it.

275
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Naha hûn sunciqan bifroşin kîloya wê çiqas e, diçe?
 
Now if you sell sunciq, how much is a kilo, how much does it
go for?

276
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Kîlo heyta çar hezaran derê.
 
A kilo goes up to four thousand.

277
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Î niha e... çar hezaran derê.
 
Right now... it goes for four thousand.

278
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Û nîv e... sê hezaran derê... Rabe hezar pêncsidî de here..
go re hebe kêm e...
 
And half... goes for three thousand... Sometimes it goes for
one thousand five hundred.. depends if it's less...

279
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Û naha... dayê we ava dawî kirî?
 
And now... mother, you finished the liquid?

280
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

281
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Û naha dema dawî ye... ev sunciq jî... de rabe wa gîştî
birinê çêkirin e.
 
And now it is the end time... this sunciq too... so get up
they all took it and made it.

282
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,000
Vê naha we dawî ye hem çêdikin?
 
Do you all make this in the end?

283
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Erê ev e dawiya wê ye ha...
 
Yes this is its end here...

284
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Em re mi zêde bî?
 
Did it get too much for us?

285
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Hê me sa kir... Hê me zêde bî, min yek anî min tê da kir...
Û me kar jî lê kir.
 
We poured it... We had too much, I brought one and put it
in... And we worked on it too.

286
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Naha... dayê hûn çêdikin herin aliyê ku derê?
 
Now... mother where are you making it to go?

287
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Erê... Tu zane ez bi xwe alîkariya jinekê dikim.
 
Yes... You know I help this woman.

288
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Ez bi xwe ne ji vir im... ez bi xwe ji Helebê me.
 
I am not from here... I am from Aleppo.

289
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Em piştî çend rojan... Ev naha çêdikin... em difiroşin ji bo
me.
 
After a few days... We make these now... we sell it for
ourselves.

290
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Dayê hûn zûde vî tiştî çêdikin?
 
Mother, have you been making this for a long time?

291
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,000
Eh ez zûde çêdikim... deh sal e min çêdikir.
 
Yes I've been making it for a long time... I have been
making it for ten years.

292
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Tu bi xwe ji vî gundî yî?
 
Are you yourself from this village?

293
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,000
Eh li vî gundî me. Bavê min çêdikir em fêr bûn.
 
Yes I am from this village. My father used to make it, we
learned.

294
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
Birakê min rahmêtî çêdikir...
 
My late brother used to make it...

295
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,000
Bapîran çêdikir, ev tiştî gişt çêdikirin...
 
The grandfathers used to make it, they made all those
things...

296
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Temam. Kê dest karê xwe bike? De rabe ev e.
 
Yes. Who will do their work? Come on, this is it.

297
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Rabe afirî ke.
 
Get up and create it.

298
00:18:47,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Ez ê xatirê xwe ji we bixwazim... Mala we ava be.
 
I will say my goodbyes to you... Bless your house.

299
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Qewet be ji we re.
 
More power to you.

300
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Saeta we xweş... Xatirê we... Xatirê we... Saeta we xweş...
 
Have a good time... Goodbye... Goodbye... Have a good
time...

301
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:59,000
Xatirê te.
 
Goodbye.

302
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Li bakurê gund çiyayê bîvê û sînorê bakurê Kurdistanê ye.
 
To the north of the village is the Bîvê mountain and the
border of Northern Kurdistan.

303
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Li rojhilat gundê Gewenda, li başûr deşta Meydanekbasê û
çiyayê Qerebelê û çiyayê Reş e.
 
To the east is the village of Gewenda, to the south is the
plain of Meydanekbasê, Qerebel mountain, and Reş mountain.

304
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Li hemberî gund ji aliyê başûr va Şeqîfê dikive.
 
Opposite the village to the south lies Şeqîfê.

305
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:26,000
Ku ew weke bajarekî kevnare û kevnar e û tanihana
kevnareşopiyên wê diyar in.
 
Which is like an ancient and old city, and its ancient
traces are still visible today.

306
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Li rojavayê gundê Welîklê û deşta Meydanê ye.
 
To the west is the village of Welîklê and the Meydan plain.

307
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:33,000
Kaniya avê li başûrê gund e.
 
The water spring is in the south of the village.

308
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Ew kanî ji aliyê Fransiyan va hatiye çêkirin û tanihana av
avê heye.
 
That spring was built by the French and still has water
today.

309
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Şivan ji pezê xwe ji ê av didin.
 
Shepherds water their sheep from it.

310
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,000
Ziyaretgeha Şêx Mûs li başûrê gund e.
 
The shrine of Şêx Mûs is in the south of the village.

311
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:49,000
Gel ji bo nexweşî û pêkhatina miradan serdana wê dikin.
 
People visit it for illnesses and the fulfillment of wishes.

312
00:20:49,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Û niha li derdora wê ya mezin ango goristana gund e.
 
And now its large surroundings, meaning the village
cemetery, is there.

313
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Merheba.
 
Hello.

314
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Ahlen û sehlen, keremkin, ser çavan, ser seran hûn hatin.
 
Welcome, please come in, you are welcome upon my eyes and
head.

315
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,000
Merheba xalê.
 
Hello, uncle.

316
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Merheba.
 
Hello.

317
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Tu çawanî, başî?
 
How are you, are you well?

318
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,000
Spas dikim, ser çavan, ser seran.
 
Thank you, upon my eyes and head.

319
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,000
Spas ji we re, tu bi xêr hatî di bernameya me de.
 
Thank you, welcome to our program.

320
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,000
Ser çavan, tu başî, tu çawanî?
 
Upon my eyes, are you well, how are you?

321
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,000
Em di karin xwe te bidin naskirin?
 
Could you introduce yourself to us?

322
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,000
Tu dikarî xwe bidî naskirin, em ê çêlekên te bipirsin.
 
Can you introduce yourself, we will ask about your cows.

323
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Rêwal e, berx e... hemû tişt...
 
Roaming animals, lambs... everything...

324
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Navê min Şerîf e.
 
My name is Şerîf.

325
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Navê te Şerîf e?
 
Your name is Şerîf?

326
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:56,000
Belê, em li gundê Baflûrê ne. Em her û her tiştî we spas
dikim, ser wê bernameyê re...
 
Yes, we are in the village of Baflûrê. We thank you for
everything, for this program...

327
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:59,000
Kêf a me gelek ji vî tiştî re hatî.
 
We are very pleased with this.

328
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Û bi taybetî axaftina te xweş e, di bernameyê de.
 
And your speaking style is especially pleasant on the
program.

329
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:08,000
Spas, spas ji we re, em gelekî kêfxweş in bi vê bernameyê,
ji ber ku em gihiştin hev du, mintaqeya Çiyayê Kurmêncan em
gihiştin hev du.
 
Thank you, thank you, we are very happy with this program,
because we reached each other, the region of Çiyayê Kurmênc,
we reached each other.

330
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:13,000
Û spas dikim, evîna we jî ev çêlek heye, hawîrdora me
heye... em kar û bar jî dikin.
 
And I thank you, for your love, there is this cow, our
surroundings... we also work.

331
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Şivanê min e, vala ye... film digrin, ê dîn e, çêlek hemûyan
di nav xwe de.
 
It is my shepherd, it is empty... they are filming, it is
crazy, the cows are all among themselves.

332
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,000
Ezê ji te bipirsim di derbarê çêlekê de.
 
I will ask you about the cows.

333
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Ku tu bi dîtina gund di derbarê wan de. Em te ji nû ve nas
bikin.
 
Because you know the village regarding them. Let's introduce
you again.

334
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,000
Navê min Şerîf e.
 
My name is Şerîf.

335
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,000
Şerîf û çî...
 
Şerîf what...

336
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,000
Şerîfê Mişê, Şerîfê Mişê...
 
Şerîf of Miş, Şerîf of Miş...

337
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:28,000
Ev çî ra ye ku tu xwedî dikî?
 
What is this that you are taking care of?

338
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Evên çêlek in. Nêrê wê heye...
 
These are cows. There is its male...

339
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,000
Çend hene? Tu çend xwedî dikî?
 
How many are there? How many do you keep?

340
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Çar in... du jê ji yên me ne, dudu ez ji ber bi şarîk dikim.
 
There are four... two of them are ours, I keep two in
partnership.

341
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Sibe, êvarî îştê ev karê min ê rojane ye.
 
Morning, evening, this is my daily work.

342
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,000
Ka tu bi roj...
 
Well, during the day...

343
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Xwedî dikin. Ez hatime der... Wexta êm didinê em ê êm
bidinê, vana...
 
We feed them. I have come out... When they feed them, we
will give them feed, these...

344
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,000
Rojê çend cara hûn êm didinê?
 
How many times a day do you feed them?

345
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,000
Em rojê sê cara êm didinê.
 
We feed them three times a day.

346
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:53,000
Yanî êmê wa jî muhaded e.
 
I mean, their feed is specified.

347
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Hûn çi didinê?
 
What do you give them?

348
00:22:54,000 --> 00:23:00,000
Em bi qasî... cureyên wê murakebe ye.
 
We give about... its types are mixed.

349
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Ev ji bo çêlekê ye, da tu bibînî ji bo çêlekê ye. Ev bi xwe
genim e, ji genim çêdibe, ji silqê çêdibe, ji ceh çêdibe, ji
garisan çêdibe.
 
This is for the cows, so you can see it's for the cows. This
itself is wheat, it is made of wheat, of chard, of barley,
of corn.

350
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:17,000
Û tiştinê din jî dîtin, taybetiyên ji bo çêlekê hene jî...
yanî gelekî baş e ji bo çêlekê.
 
And they have found other things too, there are specifics
for the cows as well... meaning it is very good for the
cows.

351
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:21,000
Tu dikarî bînî çawa ewê kar dikî bidê wan re? Çawa hûn êm
dikin?
 
Can you show how you do this work to feed them? How do you
feed them?

352
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:24,000
Êmê wan jî, muhaded e... ez rast vî bikim.
 
Their feed is also specified... let me straighten this out.

353
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Nabe em her çêlek... her êmekî şeş kîlo... şeş kîlo bixwe
evî.
 
It shouldn't be every cow... every meal six kilos... it eats
six kilos of this.

354
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,000
Her êmekî.
 
Every meal.

355
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Ev muhaded e jê re, te zêde pê de, nexweş dike, pê de,
nexweş dike.
 
This is specified for it, if you give more, it gets sick, if
you give more, it gets sick.

356
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,000
Şeş kîlo her carekê...
 
Six kilos every time...

357
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Her carekê şeş kîlo pê didî.
 
Every time you give it six kilos.

358
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,000
Yanî rojê çend caran hûn didinê?
 
So how many times a day do you feed them?

359
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:48,000
Rojê sê caran didinê. Sibehê şeş, êvarê şeş... yanê nîvrojê
ew jî...
 
We feed them three times a day. Morning six, evening six...
I mean at noon that too...

360
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,000
Hejde kîlo didinê?
 
Do you give eighteen kilos?

361
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:53,000
Sibehê şeş kîlo, êvarê şeş kîlo ye. Yanî nîvro jî em piçek
qaşikên sêvikan em didinê... sê kîloyan em didinê.
 
In the morning six kilos, in the evening six kilos. I mean,
at noon we also give some apple peels... we give three
kilos.

362
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,000
Başe, hûn tiştî didinê?
 
Okay, do you give it anything else?

363
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,000
Na, tu tiştekî tişt nin e.
 
No, there isn't anything else.

364
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,000
Tenê av e?
 
Is it just water?

365
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:59,000
Tenê av, kêm e û av e. Av zêde divê.
 
Just water, it is scarce and it is water. Water is needed a
lot.

366
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,000
Nexweşiyên kê ne?
 
What are their illnesses?

367
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Nexweşiyên kê ne, eger te... nexweş dike, divê tu... nexweş
divê pir nexweş dibe.
 
What are their illnesses, if you... it gets sick, you
must... sick, it gets very sick.

368
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:20,000
Lazim e eger te xwest... çêlek bi xwe weke zarokekî piçûk e.
Yanî tu çawa xwedî bikî, te ha jê nebe, derhal nexweş dikeve
vana.
 
It is necessary if you want... the cow itself is like a
small child. I mean, how you take care of it, if you are not
aware of it, they immediately fall sick.

369
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Anha em hazir dikin, em ê bidin cengeyan, çêlek dikin, em ê
bidin.
 
Now we are preparing, we will give it to the calves, they
are making it a cow, we will give it.

370
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,000
Bêje temaşevana, ca de ka em hemrê temaşe kin.
 
Tell the viewers, come on let's watch together.

371
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:48,000
De keremkin ka em çawa didinê.
 
Well, please come, let's see how we feed them.

372
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,000
Navê pişka vî çi tê?
 
What is the name of this part?

373
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:58,000
Neha piştre em êmê wê danîn. Evên golik in... wextê gihanî
ne, ez didoşa.
 
Well, later we put its feed down. These are calves... when
they are mature, I milk them.

374
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Dudo jinika ye.
 
Two are female.

375
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,000
Ev çî... nav çî lê dikin?
 
This what... what do they call it?

376
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,000
Ê rojan e, dudo... we... ê rojan we...
 
Every day, two... you... every day you...

377
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,000
Cinsê wan...
 
Their breed...

378
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:10,000
Çêlekên wa? Cinsê wan... yê piraniyê Danîmarkî ne.
 
Their cows? Their breed... the majority are Danish.

379
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Çêlê holandî ye. Danîmarkî saxlem e. Ev yê holandî ye,
siholendî yê saxlem ne...
 
The cow is Dutch. The Danish is healthy. This one is Dutch,
the pure Dutch is not healthy...

380
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:22,000
Yê Danîmarkî ye. Yê holandî...
 
It is Danish. The Dutch one...

381
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,000
Saxlem ev e?
 
The healthy one is this?

382
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:31,000
Saxlem ev e. Tabietê ev e jî. Danîmarkî ji xwe... gelekî baş
e. Bi xwe tabetî gelekî baş e.
 
The healthy one is this. Its nature is this too. The Danish
by itself... is very good. Naturally, it's very good itself.

383
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,000
Şiyar...
 
Şiyar...

384
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,000
Naha tu ji te hûtî çi pêk ve ji wan re?
 
Now what do you do with them from here?

385
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,000
Hemû weqta xwarin e tenê.
 
Only all the feeding time.

386
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:41,000
Tên e? Ji bo bilûrê û stranê tu nebêjî?
 
They come? For the flute and songs, won't you say anything?

387
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:45,000
Xwedê jê razî be em wusa teze şivantî ya min re, tiştkî
piçik hebû.
 
May God be pleased, thus for my new shepherd life, there was
something little.

388
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Belê eger bilûrekê em li ser çêlekên xwe... em nizanin ew
çêlek we hez dike an nake, nizanim.
 
Yes, if a flute on our cows... we don't know if that cow
likes you or not, I don't know.

389
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,000
Tu weke xwe dibêjî?
 
You play as you like?

390
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Ez tenê.
 
Just me.

391
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:57,000
Ji bilûrê tu dar ji darê çêdike, derdixe?
 
From the flute, do you make it from wood, take it out?

392
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:03,000
Na dar e, ji mîriyê, derbên me yê miriyên ser e.
 
No, it's wood, from myrtle, it's our blows of the high
myrtles.

393
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,000
Tu di kîjan derên dixî?
 
Which places do you play?

394
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,000
Erom ser e... sed heyf em merî...
 
Erom on top... a hundred pities we people...

395
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,000
Ka ev darê ji ku ye?
 
Well, where is this wood from?

396
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:16,000
Î mirê re, evî navî mirê re ye. Ser hat e...
 
The myrtle, this name is the myrtle. It came upon...

397
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:36,000
Lênxe
 
Play it.

398
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:44,000
Te çawa fêr bû? Kê te fêr kir e?
 
How did you learn? Who taught you?

399
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,000
Welleh tiştê... ez hevala bû, şivan bû, hevala bû...
 
Well, the thing... I had a friend, he was a shepherd, I had
a friend...

400
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:48,000
Te tişkî ji wan dî ye?
 
Have you seen anything from them?

401
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:52,000
Te dît, tu şivantiyê dikî, tu rûdinê tu rehet nake yek
tiştek dikî...
 
You saw, you do shepherding, you sit, you don't relax, you
do one thing...

402
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,000
Tê ji zaroka tu fêr dikî? Zikmaka tu yê xwe nexistiye?
 
Do you teach the children? You haven't taught your own?

403
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Zarok e, qet qebûl nakin. Welleh destê te nabin ez bi wext
re nabêjim.
 
It's the child, they don't accept it at all. By God, they
don't take your hand, I don't say it in time.

404
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,000
Wa yi bin e?
 
Is it this one?

405
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:04,000
Wa yi bin e. Kekê, sêrbêr kin, sêrbê kin... e, werê diçî...
 
It's this one. Brother, watch, watch... yes, go there...

406
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:14,000
Werê destê xwe bidê, ka te lîze da... nabe. Lîze lîze
bistên. Lîze da. Pêk re nabêjim... bînî te sêbî.
 
Come here, give your hand, well let him play it... no. Take
the flute. Let him play. I don't say together... bring it,
you played it.

407
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:20,000
Nabe navê pêk de, fatir e dibe...
 
Don't put the name together, it becomes sour...

408
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Gelek zehmet e. Ez tişt nebêjim te.
 
It's very difficult. Let me tell you something.

409
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:27,000
Bîst sal min we xebat kir, heta ku min va ji bo we, bîst
sal...
 
I worked with this for twenty years, until I did this for
you, twenty years...

410
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,000
Tiştkê dibêjî? Ji bo...
 
Will you say something? For...

411
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:34,000
Sipas, axaftinek, min gelek hêvî dikim, em milleta kurd
hamuyan heye...
 
Thanks, a talk, I hope a lot, we Kurdish nation all have...

412
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:48,000
Îro, rojan me ye, îro... wexta Kurdistanê ye, lazim e em
bangawazî, em tev... yek, bibe yek, mêjî bibe yek.
 
Today, it's our day, today... is the time for Kurdistan, we
must call out, we all... become one, minds become one.

413
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:52,000
Wexta Kurdistanê hatiye, û Kurdistan serkeftinê, înşelleh.
 
The time for Kurdistan has come, and Kurdistan will be
victorious, God willing.

414
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:57,000
Û serkeftin ji bo hamuyan re û ji bernameya we... destên xwe
hamuyan sipas dikim.
 
And success for everyone and for your program... I thank the
hands of you all.

415
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Em di gelekê min spas dikim.
 
We thank you very much.

416
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,000
Spas, spas daxwazim.
 
Thank you, thank you, I ask.

417
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:20,000
Xatirê te, spas.
 
Goodbye, thank you.

418
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:34,000
Nêzî 50 xanî û 500 kes li gund dijîn, û gelek kes li
bajaroka Meydanekbês û li bajarê Efrînê niştecih bûne.
 
Nearly 50 houses and 500 people live in the village, and
many people have settled in the town of Meydanekbês and the
city of Afrin.

419
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:39,000
Gundî debara jiyana xwe bi çandiniyê dikin, weke piraniya
gundên herêmê.
 
The villagers make their living through agriculture, like
most of the villages in the region.

420
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:45,000
Di serî da xizmetkirina zeviyên zeytûna û di pileya duyemîn
da xizmetkirina rezan tê.
 
Primarily by cultivating olive fields, and in the second
degree, cultivating vineyards.

421
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
Lê ev dawî, berhemên we navdar e.
 
But lately, their products are famous.

422
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:56,000
Ji banî, bastêq, qirmê, mewîj, dimis û wan berhemna li
bazarên Reco û Efrînê difroşin.
 
From dried fruit, fruit leather, grape molasses, raisins,
syrup, and they sell these products in the markets of Rajo
and Afrin.

423
00:29:56,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Di gel rez û zeytûnan, gelek kes fistiqan diçînin û xwedî
dikin.
 
Along with vineyards and olives, many people plant and tend
to pistachios.

424
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Roj baş birêz. Merhaba ji te re.
 
Good day, sir. Hello to you.

425
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:36,000
Ehlen, merhaba. Mît merhaba. Hûn bi xêr û selamet hatin li
axa welêt.
 
Welcome, hello. A hundred hellos. You have come safely and
with goodness to the homeland's soil.

426
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:46,000
Em dixwazin tiştekî ji we re şerh kin. Û ev bi nefsî me
nefsanî ye. Me pir pê de emret bûn. Û înşeallah wê feydeyek
li Kurdan jî anîbe.
 
We want to explain something to you. This is personal to us.
We have grown very old doing this. And hopefully, it will
also be useful to the Kurds.

427
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Sax bî.
 
Thank you.

428
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:52,000
Heta Kurdekî, yek gulekî, e, zanibe me gotiye çiye.
 
So that any Kurd, even a small flower, knows what we have
said.

429
00:30:52,000 --> 00:31:00,000
Em ê, berî wê yekê zûda, em rojekê hatin gundê Gêwenda, berî
evdîdî em çûn Şeqîfê de devera dî. Tenê te li ser Şeqîfê
axivî. Wê hingî.
 
We, before that early time, one day we came to the village
of Gêwenda, before that we went to Şeqîf and other areas.
Only you spoke about Şeqîf. At that time.

430
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,000
Helbest nivîsandibûn.
 
You had written poems.

431
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:06,000
Û te helbest nivîsandin. Û te wext.. li ser wextê xwe te wad
dida...
 
And you wrote poems. And you made a promise on your own
time...

432
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,000
Erê... û îro jî em ê..
 
Yes... and today we will..

433
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,000
Em hatine gundê Dûdê. Me got em ê derbasî cem te bin.
 
We have come to the village of Dûdê. We said we would stop
by to see you.

434
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,000
Biserçavan, bi can.. û mît merhaba.. ehlen we sehlen..
 
With all my heart and soul... a hundred hellos... welcome.

435
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,000
Sax bî. Em ê.. te helbesta xwe hazir kiriye yan na?
 
Thank you. Have you prepared your poem or not?

436
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,000
Hazir kiriye.
 
I have prepared it.

437
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,000
Te ev helbest ji kengî da nivîsandiye?
 
Since when did you write this poem?

438
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,000
Ji mêj va teqrîben..
 
From a long time ago, approximately..

439
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:30,000
Yanî, min yek çêkir.. min da.. Doktor Ahmed ji cerîdeya
Ronahî dişaixilî.
 
I mean, I made one.. I gave it to.. Doctor Ahmed who works
for the Ronahi newspaper.

440
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:40,000
Ahmedê Ezizî reş û qer e, doktor e. Doktorê tehlîlê ye. Min
da wî, wî bir dîwanek. Min ji wî re çendek yek du jê eyna
noka çêdikir.
 
Ahmed Ezizi, he's dark-skinned, he's a doctor. An analysis
doctor. I gave it to him, he took a divan (collection). I
was just making a couple of them for him then.

441
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:43,000
Di gund de başqe tu kes helbestvan heye?
 
Is there any other poet in the village?

442
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,000
Na. Tine...
 
No. There isn't...

443
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,000
Tu çend sal in dinivîsînî wisa?
 
How many years have you been writing like this?

444
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:54,000
Wellehî teqrîben... di heyata xwe de, ez tim bi van tiştan
re girêdayî me, êdî min dest pê kir e, wekî boş bûm. Bîst-
panzdeh bîst sal na...
 
By God, approximately... in my life, I have always been tied
to these things, so I started, when I was free. Not twenty-
fifteen twenty years...

445
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:58,000
Derketim, teqawidî ye, e.. boş im.. êdî ez kanim...
bixebitim.
 
I left, I'm retired, uh.. I'm free.. now I can... work.

446
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,000
Te bi xwe helbestên te li ser çi ye? Li ser..
 
What are your poems about? About..

447
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Li ser Kurdistanê û li ser tarîxê û li ser qehremaniya te..
 
About Kurdistan and about history and about your heroism..

448
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,000
Li ser dîrokê yanî..
 
About history, you mean..

449
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,000
Belê li ser dîrokê, erê.
 
Yes, about history, yes.

450
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:07,000
Evînî jî hene?
 
Are there love ones too?

451
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:15,000
Hene... Bi giştî ye, weke min got... bi giştî ye... her
tiştekî, qismek jê ye. Her ciz'ekî jê ye.
 
There are... In general, as I said... it's in general...
there's a part of everything. Every part of it.

452
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:22,000
Ema xaseten, li ser Kurdistanê ye. Ew e ya herî girîng e. Em
noka deng dikin e.
 
But especially, it's about Kurdistan. That is the most
important one. We are speaking up now.

453
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,000
Kerem ke..
 
Go ahead.

454
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Dengê Kurdistanê.
 
The Voice of Kurdistan.

455
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:33,000
Kurdistan ban dikî.
 
Kurdistan calls out.

456
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Li çar aliyan va ban dikî... Dibê Kurdo rabe ji xewê.
 
It calls out from all four sides... It says, Kurd, wake up
from your sleep.

457
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:50,000
Çar parçe Kurdistan e. Bi birîn e. Di bin destê dijmin da bi
nalîn e.
 
Kurdistan is four parts. It's wounded. It's moaning under
the enemy's hands.

458
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Hezar û pêncsed sal in, xwîna sor li ser Kurdistanê
diherike.
 
For one thousand five hundred years, red blood has been
flowing over Kurdistan.

459
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:03,000
Kurda... kî ye were Kurdistanê li destê dijmin xelas ke.
 
Kurds... who will come and save Kurdistan from the enemy's
hands.

460
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:08,000
Haya kînga Kurdistanê, wê xudanê xwe nas ke?
 
Until when will Kurdistan recognize its owner?

461
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:16,000
Hîv û.. rojên xweş li Kurdistanê hilhat, Kurdistan ban dikî.
 
Moon and.. good days rose in Kurdistan, Kurdistan calls out.

462
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:23,000
Alem tev da... Bi nav... heft qat, bi sîlehên dijminan hevdû
kuştin.
 
The whole world... all... seven layers, killed each other
with the enemies' weapons.

463
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:30,000
Kela û bajaran xirab kirin, çarşî û ziqaq bi xwînê şuştin.
 
They destroyed citadels and cities, they washed the markets
and alleys with blood.

464
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:39,000
Hezar qesr û mizgeft.. dêr û xan xirab kirin. Heq, hiqûqê...
miletê Kurd li nav şe'bana wenda kirin.
 
They destroyed a thousand palaces and mosques.. churches and
inns. They lost the right and law of... the Kurdish nation
among the peoples.

465
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Kurda, dîsa Kurdistan li çar aliyan ve ban dikî.
 
Kurds, Kurdistan calls out again from all four sides.

466
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:50,000
Dibê Kurdo rabe li xwe e... Kî ye were... ji destê dijmin
min xelas ke.
 
It says, Kurd, wake up.. Who will come... save me from the
enemy's hand.

467
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:56,000
Gol û herêmên min.. asê bûn serkeftin, hudûdê... dewletan
xirab bûn.
 
My lakes and regions.. became difficult and victorious, the
borders of... states were destroyed.

468
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:05,000
Hudûdê Sykes-Picot û li Cenevre... dijminan, Îngilîz
Kurdistan parçe kirin, îlxan kirin.
 
The Sykes-Picot border and in Geneva... the enemies, the
British partitioned Kurdistan, they eliminated it.

469
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:11,000
Kurdistanê delal... ji nav dijmin bi derket..
 
The beloved Kurdistan... emerged from among the enemy..

470
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:19,000
Li ser çar... parçeyê... Kurdistanê, îşq û nûr vekir...
 
Over the four... parts of... Kurdistan, love and light
shone...

471
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:24,000
Kurdino rabin ser xwe, çar parçeyê Kurdistanê bi hevgihînin.
 
Kurds, rise up, unite the four parts of Kurdistan.

472
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:29,000
Dijminan û neyaran, li ser erdê Kurdistanê, biqewtînin.
 
Kick out the enemies and foes, from the land of Kurdistan.

473
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:33,000
Xwîna dijminan, neyaran, ser Kurdistanê... biherikînin.
 
Make the blood of enemies, of foes flow over Kurdistan...

474
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:38,000
Bi xwînê hudûdê Kurdistanê, li şerq û xerbê dînin.
 
With blood, set the borders of Kurdistan, in the east and
the west.

475
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:44,000
Bi luxeta xwe yî Kurdî, bi luxeta dê û bavan, tarîxa
Kurdistanê dînin.
 
With your Kurdish language, with the language of mothers and
fathers, establish the history of Kurdistan.

476
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:49,000
Alaya rengîn, li ser çiyayên.. di..zanan... dînin.
 
Place the colorful flag, on the mountains of.. the
knowledgeable...

477
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,000
Millet şerq û xerb bi çavê serê xwe bibînin.
 
Let the nation see the east and west with their own eyes.

478
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:58,000
Millet heta bi heta... bi îbret kin... Milet bi xwa...
bibînin.
 
Let the nation make an example forever... Let the nation see
it themselves.

479
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:01,000
Kurdan rabûn ser xwê... Kurdistan ban dikê.
 
Kurds rose up... Kurdistan is calling.

480
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:05,000
Li çar parçe Kurdistanê, tedareka te dikî.
 
In the four parts of Kurdistan, they are preparing for you.

481
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Dar û ber, kevir û kuçkê Kurdistanê ban dikî dibê kurdo
were.
 
The trees and stones, rocks and pebbles of Kurdistan call
out, saying Kurd, come.

482
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:14,000
Xwîna sor... li ser Kurdistanê, li çar aliyan de herikî.
 
Red blood... flowed over Kurdistan, on all four sides.

483
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:19,000
Kurdo bi xwînê bi alim e, bi xwendinê Kurdistanê xelas ke.
 
Kurd, learn with blood, save Kurdistan with reading
(education).

484
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:22,000
Xêr û xêrata Kurdistanê.. ji destê dijmin derxe.
 
Take the goodness and blessings of Kurdistan.. out of the
enemy's hands.

485
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
Ne bese hezar û pêncsed sal in, em xizmetkar in?
 
Isn't it enough that for one thousand five hundred years, we
are servants?

486
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:31,000
Ne bese hazar pêncsed sal dijmin sermiyanê... serwetê..
Kurdan xwarin?
 
Isn't it enough that for one thousand five hundred years the
enemy ate the wealth... the resources.. of the Kurds?

487
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:35,000
Ey milletê Kurd... ko em nebin yek.. dijmin.. mezin e.
 
Oh Kurdish nation... if we do not unite.. the enemy.. is
big.

488
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:38,000
Li ser vê erdê.. kesek wek war nîne dîtine.
 
On this earth.. no one has seen a place like ours.

489
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:44,000
Heyfa we Kurdan.. hezar sal in, ji kêlem û ecem û tirkan re,
dimirin.
 
It is a pity for you Kurds.. for a thousand years, dying for
the neighbors, Persians, and Turks.

490
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:47,000
Di xwîna xwe rijandin, ez çi bikim... gunehkar kirin.
 
Shedding their own blood, what can I do... they made us
sinners.

491
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:53,000
Te gelek dirêj nivîsandiye... wa ye sipas.. gelek dirêj te
nivîsandiye.
 
You have written it very long... here, thanks.. you have
written it very long.

492
00:35:53,000 --> 00:36:00,000
Erê.. pir e jê.. Û înşeallah jî... Kurd... e bi meydanê
keve, wê heqîqeta wê..
 
Yes.. there's a lot of it.. And hopefully too... the Kurd...
will enter the arena, its truth will..

493
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:03,000
Wê ya kamil bibe. Wê.. dibê..
 
It will become complete. He.. says..

494
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
"Leyse arun... en yebîtu", ewa gotina... Yûsif el Ezma...
 
"Leyse arun... en yebîtu", that is the saying of... Yusuf
al-Azma...

495
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Kî..? gava çû.. wexta birin ber hebsa Romê.. bankir, ew yên
çavê min vakin, destê min jî, yên zincîr kirine...
 
Who..? when he went.. when they took him to the Rome
prison.. he called out, open those eyes of mine, and my
hands, which are chained...

496
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:21,000
Nav lê nan el-recul el-mecnûn. Birin ber.. qayfe hebsa Romê
ji bo yariya..
 
They named him "the crazy man". They took him in front of..
the gate of the Rome prison for mockery..

497
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:27,000
Got bes ew çavê min vakin.. Çav vekirin.. destê xwe jî..
vekir.. ban.. hebsekir..
 
He said just open my eyes.. They opened his eyes.. he also
opened his hands.. called.. imprisoned..

498
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Got; "Ya zelamê secnî, xeyyemû înnenî nehwê zelema".
 
He said; "Oh darkness of the prison, set up tents, for I am
moving towards the darkness".

499
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:37,000
Şînda sê... zindanan, hebsa birîn min we ra.. ser min, çadir
bi aze, berte tîn.
 
Behind three... dungeons, they cut a prison for me for you..
over me, a tent in the open, they bring to you.

500
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:42,000
Got, "Leyse 'arun en yebîtu, fîl cîbelî, înnemêl aru, en
yebîta ebid e" ...
 
He said, "It is not a shame to sleep in the mountains, but
the shame is to sleep as a slave"...

501
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:46,000
Got ne ar e... însanê... cîbê... rabe.. çîya.. mehkûm şketa
be.
 
He said it's not a shame... for a person... to wake up.. in
the mountains.. condemned in caves.

502
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:50,000
Got, ar e.. însan.. umr di bin destî dijmin de, bikule, qeyt
derbas ke.
 
He said, it is a shame.. for a person.. to suffer their
whole life under the enemy's hand, to pass the time bound in
chains.

503
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:55,000
Got "ya ranîne qeydû ziyidnî nexmetan teşcî fuadî"...
 
He said "Oh the clanking of the chains, increase me in a
melody that encourages my heart"...

504
00:36:55,000 --> 00:37:01,000
Got ya zincîrî... dest û lingê min î... bişkestin.. dilê min
de.. milê xwe.. bi hesibim... ev a.. çi pa girtî.
 
He said oh chains... breaking my hands and legs... in my
heart.. my shoulder.. I consider... this.. what holds my
feet.

505
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:15,000
[Music/Transition]
 
[Music/Transition]

506
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:22,000
Her wiha, sê şehîd ji gund hene. Şehîd Demhat, Şehîd Xwînrej
û Şehîd Ronahî.
 
Additionally, there are three martyrs from the village.
Martyr Demhat, Martyr Xwînrej, and Martyr Ronahi.

507
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:26,000
Komîna gund bi navê Şehîd Demhat hatiye binavkirin.
 
The village commune has been named after Martyr Demhat.

508
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:34,000
Hisên Nasir ango Kêl Heso di serweriya Fransizan de, sê
mîlîsên Fransî bi dêtê de kuştin.
 
Huseyin Nasir, also known as Kel Heso, during the French
mandate, killed three French militiamen.

509
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:39,000
Piştre leşkerên Fransî hatin gund û bi firokeyan topbaran
kirin.
 
Afterwards, French soldiers came to the village and
bombarded it with airplanes.

510
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:43,000
Ev di derdora sala 1937'an de bû.
 
This was around the year 1937.

511
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:51,000
Rêjeya xwendinê di gund de baş e. Lewra zêdetirî pêncî kesî
bawernameyên zanîngehê di beşên curbicur de stendin.
 
The literacy rate in the village is good. Therefore, more
than fifty people have obtained university degrees in
various departments.

512
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:55,000
Û gelek kesan jî xwendina amadeyî qedandine.
 
And many people have also completed high school education.

513
00:37:55,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Hêjayî têbîniyê ye ku her gundên meyî damm bûne, weke yek
gund tê naskirin.
 
It is worth noting that all our combined villages are known
as one village.

514
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:05,000
Ango weke bajarokekî mezin û nûjen li ser deşteke fireh ava
bûye.
 
That is, it has been built like a large and modern town on a
wide plain.

515
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Û dê di pêşerojê de bibe bajarokekî pêşketî.
 
And in the future, it will become an advanced town.

516
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:31,000
[Music/Transition]
 
[Music/Transition]

517
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:41,000
Belê naha jî, em ji gundê Dûdê derketin. Me xwest em derbasî
cihên avê lê hebin bibin.
 
Yes, now too, we have left the village of Dude. We wanted to
move on to places where there is water.

518
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:47,000
Me qesd kirin... gotin, bîrek li vir heye. Em hatin... Fatme
jî bi me re derbas bû. Metê merhaba ji te re.
 
We intended to... they said, there is a well here. We
came... Fatma also came with us. Auntie, hello to you.

519
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,000
Merhaba. Merhaba.
 
Hello. Hello.

520
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:54,000
Naha ka des... destê xwe... ka... Naha te berê min re got tu
dihatî vê bîrê li vir...
 
Now let's... your hand... let's... Now you told me earlier
that you used to come to this well here...

521
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,000
Eê.. em dihatinê.
 
Yes.. we used to come.

522
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,000
Hûn kengî dihatin? Saet çend da we dihatinê?
 
When did you use to come? At what time did you use to come?

523
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:00,000
Êvarî...
 
In the evening...

524
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,000
Hn?
 
Hmm?

525
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:05,000
Nîvê şevê û... Manê.. ta tarî...
 
In the middle of the night and... I mean.. until dark...

526
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:07,000
Wekî din hûn çawa dihatin?
 
How else did you use to come?

527
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Em dihatin... Me kinc dişûştin, me serê xwe dişûştin qurban.
 
We used to come... We used to wash clothes, we used to wash
our heads (hair), dear.

528
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:15,000
Av tine bû...
 
There was no water...

529
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:17,000
Metê tu çend salan tu hatî vêrê?
 
Auntie, how many years did you come here?

530
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,000
Bîst sal in hene...
 
It's been twenty years...

531
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,000
Tu bîst salan tu hatî vê bîrê.
 
You came to this well for twenty years.

532
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:20,000
Erê..
 
Yes..

533
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:22,000
Naha gelek tişt hatin bîra te, dema ku te dît hatî vira..
 
Now many things came to your mind, when you saw you came
here..

534
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:28,000
Hatin lê... Işta di bîra me de we di bîra me...
 
They did... Just like we remember, you remember...

535
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:31,000
Me kinc dişûştin... me serê xwe dişûştin, qurban.
 
We used to wash clothes... we used to wash our heads, dear.

536
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Me av dibir malê... Lê...
 
We used to take water to the house... Look...

537
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:39,000
Êê hûn kî bûn.. hûn dihatin wê demê de?
 
Uh, who were you all.. who used to come at that time?

538
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:44,000
Em dihatin... Jin dihatin... Mêr dihatin...
 
We used to come... Women used to come... Men used to come...

539
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:48,000
Em dihatin avê... em dihatin vir...
 
We used to come for water... we used to come here...

540
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,000
Merhaba ji te re.
 
Hello to you.

541
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:51,000
Merhaba, ehlen û sehlen..
 
Hello, welcome..

542
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:52,000
Em te nas bikin.
 
Let's get to know you.

543
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:58,000
Mamê te.. Selam li we re. Hûn bi xêr hatin axa welêt û em..
serkeftinê ji bo we.. daxwaz in..
 
Your uncle.. Greetings to you. You are welcome to the
homeland's soil and we.. wish success for you..

544
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,000
Sax bî... Em te nas bikin.
 
Thank you... Let's get to know you.

545
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Reşîdê Ehmed ê.
 
Reşîdê Ehmed.

546
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
Ereb Bavê Seyfedîn.
 
Ereb Bavê Seyfedîn.

547
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:04,000
Sarinc, apê Reşîd, ti tiştekî li ser sarincê...
 
Cistern, uncle Reşîd, you something about the cistern...

548
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:07,000
Apê Reşîd nîha, çend sarinc hebin li vir a?
 
Uncle Reşîd now, how many cisterns might be here?

549
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:13,000
Sarinc, belkî ser pênciya ra ye, di vê derê berê bajêr bû,
bajarê Şeqîf wê ra digotin.
 
Cisterns, maybe there are over fifty, here it was a city
before, they used to call it Şeqîf city.

550
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:18,000
Belê carekê rojekê em hatin Mehdiyê, eva Bajarê Şeqîf
digotin.
 
Yes once one day we came to Mehdiyê, they used to call this
Şeqîf City.

551
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:25,000
Zemanê me, kurmancên me û berê tim ji vî derî xizex xwe hez
dikirin. Xwestin tim di siyê da bin, wek kûsan.
 
In our time, our Kurds, before they always liked secluded
places from this place. They wanted to always be in the
shade, like turtles.

552
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Î noko jî... î noko na na. Î noko ku dixwazin bi hevdû ra
rûyê hevdu bin. Xaniyê xwe çê dikin.
 
But those of now... no no. Those of now want to be face to
face with each other. They build their houses.

553
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Vê maneyê da dixwazin li hember rûyê bin.
 
In this sense they want to be facing each other.

554
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:38,000
Û hawna jî belkî pêncî bîr zêdetir li vê mentiqê ye.
 
And these maybe there are more than fifty wells in this
area.

555
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:43,000
Berê bajarê Şeqîf digotin. Heta nîha edbetên xwemazin li vir
in...
 
In the past they called it Şeqîf city. Until now its great
ruins are here...

556
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:46,000
Banê Cewşê heye, şikestî da ye.
 
There is Banê Cewşê, in the ruins.

557
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:50,000
Cihê xwe li wir da ye, herezê xwe jî li ser piştekî ban
bilind bû.
 
Its place is there, its watchman was also on a high roof's
back.

558
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Wê çaxê nedîbû, bûq lê dixistin.
 
At that time it wasn't seen, they used to blow the horn.

559
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:57,000
Her herezek, tilîyek li vir e, yek li vir e, yek li vir e...
yek li vir e...
 
Every watchman, one finger is here, one is here, one is
here... one is here...

560
00:40:57,000 --> 00:41:00,000
Hawa tilî, seft a Banê Cewşê digotin. Î dido jî...
 
Like fingers, they called it the row of Banê Cewşê. The
second one too...

561
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:03,000
Uli hîn, î sêyê Karzin.
 
And the others, the third is Karzin.

562
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Î çara Keleha cem gewenda.
 
The fourth is the Castle near the Gewenda.

563
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
Î pêncê, be'îve, xofî gundî dido.
 
The fifth is Be'îve, Xofî village of two.

564
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:14,000
Û hewîrmana jî ev mihafeze dikin. Me'nî kesek taq çilo, î
zingikê lê nake.
 
And these protect its surroundings. Meaning no one can
attack them, cannot ring the bell.

565
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:18,000
Me'nî em xwe rûk bi vê... me'nî herba xwe di nav da xweşêr
in.
 
Meaning we face this... meaning their war inside is hidden.

566
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Û î din, î şeşê, Banî Birkê heye, xofî kûsava...
 
And the other, the sixth, there is Banî Birkê, Xofî
Kûsava...

567
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:30,000
Li vî derê qaîdeyi wana li Sûrê hebî, Sûrê vê ra dibî. Sûrê
vî ra hebî.
 
Here their rule was in the Wall, they called it its Wall. It
had a Wall.

568
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:36,000
Yanî bûn heft. Ev bûq lê dixistin. Vî telefon vî dikir, vî
ban vî dikir, vî ban vî dikir, vî ban vî dikir.
 
Meaning they became seven. These blew the horn. This one
called that one, this one called that one, this one called
that one.

569
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:40,000
Îşaret didan havdû. Hîs digehaştin havdû.
 
They gave signals to each other. The news reached each
other.

570
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Heta ku ê vê derê dişandin Lêçê, digehaşt Axdapê. Li wir jî
cihê xwe hebûn.
 
Until the one here sent it to Lêçê, it reached Axdapê. They
had their places there too.

571
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Li vê derê, rûyê dide piştê. Wextê êvarê jî diftilî, dîsa
rûyê dide piştê.
 
Here, it turns its face back. When evening came it turned,
again it turns its face back.

572
00:41:54,000 --> 00:42:00,000
Wê çaxê meşên gende dûbil bû. Him vir va diçû rûyê dide
piştê, him vî va dihat rûyê dide piştê.
 
At that time their paths were double. Both going this way it
turns its face back, coming this way it turns its face back.

573
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:07,000
Rû caran nadîbû. Vê maneyê da meşê xwe dûbil bû, di meş da
birin.
 
The face was never seen. In this sense their path was
double, they transported in walking.

574
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:10,000
Ev dîrokek kevn e ev a.
 
This is an old history.

575
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:15,000
Ha va kevn e. Bi hezar sal e, ev. Ev dibe... goya... îşta
romada dibin.
 
Yes this is old. It's a thousand years, this. This is...
like... as they say, from the Romans.

576
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Yanî ku gelek kanî tine ne, tenê hema bîr in.
 
Meaning that there aren't many springs, they are just wells.

577
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:23,000
Erê bîr in. Pêş û paş ew Banî Cewşê, bi seda bîr hene.
 
Yes they are wells. Before and behind that Banî Cewşê, there
are hundreds of wells.

578
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:27,000
Heta haliyen nîha, noko, bi seda bîr hene, vê derê jî qeder
bajêr bûn.
 
Even currently now, now, there are hundreds of wells, this
place was also somewhat a city.

579
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:37,000
Em ê vegerin cem dayê. Dayê, ka... çi berê çi dihat bîra te?
Dema te dît te hatî te hatî vê avê... nîha jî tu hatiye...
Çi tê bîra te?
 
We will return to mother. Mother, let's... what did you
remember from before? When you saw, you came, you came to
this water... now you've come too... What comes to your
mind?

580
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:40,000
Tu kî ve da hatiyîne?
 
Where have you come from?

581
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:46,000
Hevalên me gund bûn, cîran bûn, em dehatin, em dehatin avê,
me kinc li vê derê dişuştin, li vir.
 
Our friends were villages, were neighbors, we used to come,
we used to come to the water, we used to wash clothes here,
here.

582
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:53,000
Erê, me radixistin, hişk dibûn, me bar dikirin, me hîn av jî
bi xwe re dibrin, em diçûn. Av tine bû.
 
Yes, we used to lay them out, they would dry, we used to
load them, we used to take water with us too, we would go.
There was no water.

583
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:56,000
Yanî her dema wek av wek gere bûyîn dihatin vêr dibirin?
 
Meaning whenever water was like a necessity, you used to
come here and take it?

584
00:42:56,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Lê! Her pêncşem. Em kîba dihatin na. Her pêncşem.
 
Yes! Every Thursday. We and whoever came. Every Thursday.

585
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
Pêncşem e?
 
Is it Thursday?

586
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:07,000
Pêncşem em dihatin avê, avê vexwarinê ew her ro dibir.
 
Thursday we used to come to the water, the drinking water
they used to take every day.

587
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:09,000
Çarnicû avî xelas dibî, me dibrin.
 
The water cisterns would finish, we used to take it.

588
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:14,000
Vê demê te digote me av xwa dibir, we avê bi çi dibir?
 
At that time you were saying we took our water, what did you
take the water with?

589
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:16,000
Te digot li wê hevalên te...
 
You were saying there your friends...

590
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:22,000
Li wê hevalên me, îşta jin bûn, em pir bûn em dehatin. A kî
bim kî bim... Lê.
 
There our friends, like that were women, we were many we
used to come. Whoever I could be... Yes.

591
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,000
Xweş in ha hevalên te?
 
Are your friends well?

592
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:27,000
Xweş, î heyî miriye, î heye xweş e îşta.
 
Well, there are those who died, there are those who are
well, like that.

593
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:30,000
Rehma xudê li miriyên we ke, ê dijîn jî...
 
May God have mercy on your dead ones, and those who live...

594
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:35,000
Berf barî sê çar mehanga me habîn.
 
It snowed, we had it for three four months.

595
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:39,000
Berf barî ko xelas dibî, em kî diçûn avê da na.
 
The snow snowed until it was finished, we would go for
water.

596
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:42,000
Me rabî, berf li qabê ye, ez û kulfetê xwe bim,
 
We got up, the snow is at the ankles, it was me and my
family,

597
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:48,000
Me her yekî telîsek dest xwe ra kir, em çûn pûzê xarabê lê,
qerf tu zane?
 
We each took a sack in our hand, we went to the corner of
the ruins, do you know frost?

598
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:57,000
Me telîsên xwe jê têje kir, me li pişta xwe da û em hatin.
 
We filled our sacks from it, we put it on our backs and we
came.

599
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:00,000
Me da dewarê xwe.
 
We gave it to our animals.

600
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,000
Ê wî demê de berf pir dibarî li vir ha?
 
So at that time, it snowed a lot here?

601
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:09,000
Lê, dibarî lê... Ha hawna diket... dibarî.
 
Yes, it used to snow, yes... Ha like this it fell... it used
to snow.

602
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,000
Nîha berf jî tine.
 
Now there is no snow either.

603
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:14,000
Noko berf jî tine... qet tine.
 
Now there is no snow either... none at all.

604
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:18,000
Ê rojên berê xweş bû lê nîhako?
 
Were the days of the past good, or now?

605
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:22,000
Î da em wa dibîn, canê noko ji wa dibin, em dibîn berê rind
bûn.
 
Those then we were like that, the souls of now are also like
that, we say the past was good.

606
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:25,000
Ew qocafên me dîtî me digot rind bûn dîsa.
 
Those old folks we saw, we said they were good again.

607
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:30,000
Ema berê kareba jê tinebû ba kî... Jiyana berê xweştir bû
yanî. Lê...
 
But in the past there was no electricity or anything... The
life of the past was better, meaning. Yes...

608
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:38,000
Yanî berê... noko ciwan dibêjin noko xweş e, em dibêjin berê
xweş e. Lê.
 
Meaning the past... now the youth say now is good, we say
the past is good. Yes.

609
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:41,000
Dibêjin her zemanekî padşahê xwe heye.
 
They say every time has its own king.

610
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:45,000
Erê. Her zemanekî paşakî xwe heye. Erê.
 
Yes. Every time has its own king. Yes.

611
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:48,000
Mala te ava, me seetek xweş da ye, tu jî xweş.
 
Bless your house, we had a good hour, you be well too.

612
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:51,000
Spas ji te ra jî, spas ji te ra jî.
 
Thank you to you too, thank you to you too.

613
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:54,000
Seeta te xweş. Em ê xatirê xwe ji temaşevana jî bixwazin.
 
Have a good hour. We will ask for our leave from the viewers
too.

614
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:58,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, li vir jî em ê geşt û dîtina xwe ya
bernameya xwe...
 
Yes esteemed viewers, here too our tour and seeing of our
program...

615
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:03,000
Li vir jî em ê xatirê xwe bixwazin, heya hefteyekî din de...
 
Here too we will ask for our leave, until another week...

